</HL>
<DATE>
05/14/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   PCLB
</CO>
<IN>
BUYBACKS, REDEMPTIONS, SWAP OFFERS (BBK)
</IN>
<LP>
   SAN DIEGO -- Price Co. said it has acquired 747,500 shares
of its common stock since February, bringing the total number
of shares it has repurchased to 1,247,500.
   The 747,500 shares were acquired by the members-only
discount department-store chain in two phases, with 207,500
of them bought at an average price of $38.50 during the
latter part of the second quarter ended March 18, 1990, and
the remaining 540,000 shares acquired at an average price of
$33.125 during the current third quarter.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   All of the purchases were made pursuant to a previously
announced board authorization to acquire up to an aggregate
of $50 million of any of the company's outstanding
securities.
