   Credit Rating:
   S&amp;P Takes Sotheby's
   Off CreditWatch List
</HL>
<DATE>
05/14/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C15
</SO>
<CO>
   BID
</CO>
<IN>
CDS, INTEREST RATES, COMMERCIAL PAPER (FIN)
</IN>
<LP>
   NEW YORK -- Standard &amp; Poor's Corp. said it affirmed
Sotheby's Inc.'s A-1 commercial paper rating and removed it
from CreditWatch, where it was placed April 26 with negative
implications.
   The review was prompted by the company's planned $142.8
million acquisition of the extensive art inventory of the
Pierre Matisse Gallery.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   S&amp;P had said the move exposed the Sotheby's Holdings Inc.
unit to a "somewhat higher business risk because it more
directly exposes the company to future art price volatility."
   But S&amp;P now has concluded that "the impact of this
transaction is not significant enough to warrant a downgrade.
Given Sotheby's strong earnings and cash flow, S&amp;P believes
that lower financial leverage will be quickly restored."
   In New York Stock Exchange composite trading Friday,
Sotheby's Holdings closed at $17.50 a share, up 50 cents.
</TEXT>
