   Business Brief -- Security Pacific Corp.:
   Unit Gets Certain Assets,
   Liabilities of Ailing Thrift
</HL>
<DATE>
05/14/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A2
</SO>
<CO>
   SPC
</CO>
<IN>
SAVINGS AND LOANS, THRIFTS, CREDIT UNIONS (SAL)
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<GV>
FEDERAL GOVERNMENT (FDL)
</GV>
<LP>
   Security Pacific National Bank said it acquired certain
assets and assumed certain liabilities of Washington Savings
&amp; Loan Association from the Resolution Trust Corp.
   Los Angeles-based Security Pacific said it will receive
about $69 million in deposits from the RTC in the
transaction.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Washington Savings &amp; Loan, based in Stockton, Calif., has
been in conservatorship with the RTC since April 1989. The
10-year-old thrift has four branches and about 7,000
customers in the Stockton area.
   Security Pacific Bank is the principal operating unit of
Security Pacific Corp., the nation's fifth-largest bank
holding company with more than $86 billion in assets.
