<LP>
   SUNWEST FINANCIAL SERVICES Inc. said it recorded additions
to loan-loss reserves and other charges totaling $7 million
due to a continuing regulatory exam, leaving the company with
net income of $2.1 million for the four-month period ended
April 30. The total for the charges was misstated in Friday's
edition.
   (See: "OTC Focus: Market Ends on Highs, Index Up 1.86; Sun
Microsystems Leads Most-Active List" -- WSJ May 11, 1990)
</LP>
<TEXT>
   ---
   NWNL Cos. reported net income, after securities losses, of
$1.11 a share, compared with an average estimate by analysts
over the previous 30 days of $1 a share, resulting in a
positive surprise of 11%. In Friday's Quarterly Earnings
Surprises table, the estimate was incorrect because of a data
base error at Zacks Investment Research. As a result, the
company's earnings were mistakenly listed as a negative
surprise.
   (See: "Quarterly Earnings Surprises" -- WSJ May 11, 1990)
   ---
   LIFETIME Corp. filed a registration statement with the
Securities and Exchange Commission for an offering that
includes 960,688 shares owned by company management. In
Friday's edition, the ownership of the shares was listed
incorrectly.
   (See: "Recent SEC Filings" -- WSJ May 11, 1990)
